    <stitle>AIR COMPRESSOR: MIDLAND MODELS EL-1300 AND EL-1600 - OPERATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>OPERATION</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="operate" graphiccount="0">
            <title>GOVERNOR OPERATION</title>
            <para>The governor, operating in conjunction with the air compressor unloading mechanism, automatically
                controls air pressure in the air brake system between the predetermined maximum and minimum air
                pressures.
            </para>
            <para>The compressor runs continually while the engine operates, but air compression is controlled by the
                governor which stops or starts compression when the maximum or minimum pressures are reached.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
